Info returns the info for the current target.

``/Info:
func (d *DB) Info() Info {
  return d.info
}
``

info gets the db info for a given target.

``/info:
func info(target string) (Info, error) {
  ``.``
}
``

open the .dbc file.

``
  b, err := os.ReadFile("/home/max/.dbc")
  if err != nil { return Info{}, err }
``

unmarshal the yaml.

``
  cnf := Conf{}
  err = yaml.Unmarshal(b, &cnf)
  if err != nil { return Info{}, err }
``

return the info for target.

``
  for targ, info := range cnf {
    //fmt.Println("t: ", targ)
    if targ == target {
      info.Target = targ
      return info, nil
    }
  }
``

target not found.

``
  return Info{}, errors.New(fmt.Sprintf("target %s not found.", target))
``

