``
  
 
connstr sticks together a connection string from db info.

``/connstr:
func connstr(info Info) string {
  ``.``
}
``

go by db type.

``
  if info.Type == "sqlite3" {
    return info.Database
  } else if info.Type == "mssql" {
    ``mssql``
  }
``

for mssql, url seems to be the preferred format, see
https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/microsoft/go-mssqldb

the database name is passed as url query value (the stuff behind the ? in the url).

``./mssql:
    vals := url.Values{}
    vals.Add("database", info.Database)
``

stitch the url together.

``
    u := &url.URL {
      Scheme: "sqlserver",
      User: url.UserPassword(info.User, info.Password),
      Host: fmt.Sprintf("%s:%d", info.Host, info.Port),
      RawQuery: vals.Encode(),
    }
    return u.String()
``

if type unknown, return empty string for now. todo error?

``../
    return ""
``

